If it's not a bug, please remove the template and elaborate the issue in your own words.
-->

![downloadprevversion_2016-10-18_14-59-32](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/19892435/19492189/b1ef45c6-9543-11e6-8055-cd0a79fd81af.jpg)
## Steps to reproduce

Click on either of the "Get PowerShell" - Download "MSI" Platform links: "Windows 10.." or "Windows 8.1..".
## Expected behavior

To download PowerShell-6.0.0-alpha.11-*.msi
## Actual behavior

It will download previous version: PowerShell-6.0.0-alpha.11-*.msi

Workaround: Go to the PowerShell Release page:
[https://github.com/PowerShell/PowerShell/releases/tag/v6.0.0-alpha.11]
## Environment data

Windows 10 Pro Insider Preview Build 14946
